Nyeri leaders say they recognise Agriculture CS Mwangi Kiunjuri as one of their own though his political base is in Laikipia county. Kiunjuri attended the fourth Nyeri  Prayer Breakfast meeting at Green Hills Hotel in Nyeri on Monday. He was warmly welcomed by the Nyeri fraternity. The meeting was attended by leaders from the county and the business community. Kiunjuri was invited to Nyeri as the chief guest at the meeting to share ideas on how to keep leaders united to achieve development. moved from devolution The CS has connections to the people of Nyeri. His wife comes fom Tetu in Nyeri. Kiunjuri is one of the most respected leaders in the county and is also popular in Laikipia. However, in November last year, some leaders from Nyeri had asked President Uhuru Kenyatta to drop him from his Cabinet. They wanted the President to appoint a person from Nyeri. But they have changed their tune. On Monday, speakers praised Kiunjuri. Mathira MP Rigathi Gachagua commended him and urged him to ensure Nyeri benefits first as he settles in his new docket. Kiunjuri was moved from the Devolution ministry. “Charity begins at home. You are part and parcel of Nyeri county. Let Nyeri start enjoying the fruits of your ministry before other counties,” Gachagua said. The MP thanked the President for appointing Kiunjuri, ICT Cabinet Secretary Joe Mucheru, Principal Secretary Nicholas Muraguri and Head of the Public Service Joseph Kinyua. Gachagua said it is enough reward for the people of Nyeri. He said Parliament is ready to approve the names of the nominees forwarded by the President so they can get down to work. Nyeri Governor Mutahi Kahiga and MPs Ngunjiri Wambugu (Nyeri Town), Gichuhi Mwangi (Tetu) and Gichuki Mugambi (Othaya) also attended the event.